            <div corresp="#c4229f2">
                <head>RUANDA:</head>
                <table>
                    <row role="label">
                        <cell>PREV. OFFICE.</cell>
                        <cell>NAME.</cell>
                        <cell>OFFICE.</cell>
                        <cell>STATE.</cell>
                        <cell>CAREER OR NON-CAREER.</cell>
                        <cell>DATE OF APPOINTMENT.</cell>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>REMARKS.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Ruanda district, E. Africa between Belgium Congo and Tanganyika;
                            formerly part of German East Africa;</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Since 1919 associated with Urundi as Ruanda-Ruundi and administered by
                            Belgium, as a League of Nations mandate 1919-45, as a U.N. trust
                            territory since 1946.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Department Mailing Notice of Nov. 2, 1960. The first American
                            Consulate has been established in the UN Trust Territory of
                            Ruanda-Urundi which is under Belgian Administration</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>(See Mailing Notice in Belgium Country File)</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>The name of the capital city of the Kingdom of Burundi was changed
                            from Usumbura to</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Bujumbura in the constitution drawn up by the newly independent
                            country. The Department</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>of State concurred with the U.S. Board on Geographic Names to
                            recognize this change</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>on March 6, 1964.</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </div>
